node.text: @kiacooks credits her mom and grandma for instilling in her a love of good food and cooking, and in today’s episode of Secret Family Recipe, Kia makes one of her grandma’s signature dishes, Chicken & Stuff, with an assist from her mom. Along the way, Kia tweaks things here and there (blanched green beans instead of canned; sautéed chicken instead of boiled) to make the recipe her own while she and her mom talk about the origins of this delicious dish with the whimsical name. Tap the link in our bio for Kia’s family recipe. #thekitchn

node.title: Secret Family Recipe: Chicken & Stuff with @kiacooks

node.text:
“I think having things that are more about where they come from and how they’re made, then a blanket statement of what’s ‘healthy’ and what isn’t. So many people could say that eating bread and butter isn’t ‘healthy,’ but I find it nourishing if it’s really good, fresh bread. And then I believe in indulgence, obviously. I’m in the business that indulgence is okay. You just want to have good indulgence with real ingredients. And then when you indulge, you indulge — no holding back.”
